TEXT_83=You may have heard that you can get tetanus if you are injured by a rusty nail. This is true only if the nail is dirty and has the tetanus bacteria on it. It is the dirt on the nail, not the rust, that carries the risk\u00A0of tetanus.
TEXT_82=If you have been injured outside or in any way that makes contact with soil likely, contact your health care provider\u00A0about your risk\u00A0of getting\u00A0tetanus infection. Injuries and wounds should be thoroughly cleaned right away. If the tissue of the wound is dying, a doctor will need to remove the tissue.
TEXT_81=Older teenagers and adults who get injuries, especially puncture-type wounds, should\u00A0get a tetanus\u00A0booster if it has been\u00A0more than 10 years since the last booster.
TEXT_80=Td vaccine or Tdap vaccine is used to maintain immunity in those age\u00A07 and older. Tdap vaccine should be given once,\u00A0before age 65, as a substitute for Td for those who have not had Tdap. Td boosters are recommended every 10 years starting at age 19.
